Here are high-level bullet points you can give your agent for HTML generation (Outlook-safe):

Use table-based layouts, not div-based designs
Keep design simple and fixed-width (avoid complex responsiveness)
Write inline CSS only (no <style> tags or external CSS)
Stick to basic, widely supported CSS properties
Use standard system fonts (e.g., Arial, Verdana)
Ensure all images use absolute URLs
Define explicit widths/heights for elements and images
Avoid modern web features (Flexbox, Grid, animations, etc.)
Generate HTML as email-friendly, not web-page style
Ensure output is compatible with Microsoft Outlook rendering
